      "writtenOn": "2026-02-16T07:27:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "since bmcweb has it\u0027s own logging functions, does it make sense to make a special one which prints under the condition that something like `--verbose` is passed to the bmcweb commandline?\n\nSomething like `BMCWEB_LOG_VERBOSE`\n\nHaving such a facility would avoid creating bit rot here and solve the use-case of \u0027we have logs which are seldom useful\u0027\n\nOtherwise a meson option or the old `static bool debug` could also solve it without hiding this code from parsing + typechecking stage.",
      "revId": "9e14b4bf335d6af2b94377e531e97543b5b2b731",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
