      "writtenOn": "2026-02-17T01:19:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not really interested in supporting such a CLI argument.  The problem of bit rot in these doesn\u0027t seem like it will be much of an issue in practice if they\u0027re commented out.\n\nIf we want to have some kind of per-subsystem logging, that\u0027s something we should look at holistically, but I\u0027m not that interested in it.  99% of the time I turn on the max log level to debug an issue, or promote a suspected log statement up to ERROR.  It\u0027s relatively rare that there are so many log statements that I need to drop the verbosity down.\n\nIf your or other peoples experience differ, I\u0027m happy to have that discussion;  I\u0027m not interested in implementing something complex for this here.",
      "parentUuid": "65013bd7_0bdcb4e8",
      "revId": "9e14b4bf335d6af2b94377e531e97543b5b2b731",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
